<subSubSection lastPageId="25" lastPageNumber="623" pageId="24" pageNumber="622" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="24.[1454,2489,3449,3478]" lastBlockId="25.[700,1294,290,718]" lastPageId="25" lastPageNumber="623" pageId="24" pageNumber="622">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1454,1608,3449,3478]" pageId="24" pageNumber="622">Taxonomy.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authorityName="Thomas" authorityYear="1910" box="[1624,1740,3449,3478]" class="Mammalia" family="Muridae" genus="Taterillus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="24" pageNumber="622" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Taterillus</taxonomicName>
tranier: Dobigny et al., 2003, Dilly, south-western Mali The most recently described species of the genus, 7. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Dobigny, Granjon, Aniskin, Ba &amp; Volobouev" authorityYear="2003" box="[912,1005,329,363]" class="Mammalia" family="Muridae" genus="Taterillus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="25" pageNumber="623" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="tranieri">tranieri</taxonomicName>
is characterized by a unique chromosomal formula. Monotypic.
</paragraph>
